&lt;p&gt;Part time - 7.5 hours per week &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Young People’s Diabetes Service within Poole hospital site are looking to employ a clinical psychologist to work as part of their team for one day a week for one year to cover the current post holder’s Maternity leave until the end of December 2021.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is exciting times for our service as we have just embarked on a joint venture as a newly formed University Hospital Dorset, and are looking to work more closely with colleagues at Bournemouth Diabetes and Endocrine Centre.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note: if this job requires you to have a DBS check to enable you to properly fulfil the requirements of the job, on appointment you will be required to repay the cost of obtaining a DBS check and this amount will be reclaimed from your salary.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date: 16/11/2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Provisional interview week commencing: 30/11/2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested and would like to discuss this further, please contact Mrs Jo Dalton (Diabetes Nurse Specialist) on 0300 019 8759 and/or Dr Mike Masding (Consultant Physician) on 0300 019 2767&lt;/p&gt;
